	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, May 14th 6:33 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>You are going to love this if you haven't heard already...<br><br>To make these you need an Artisan's Seal. Simple Enough...<br><br>1 Blue Diamond<br>1 Black Sapphire<br>1 Diamond<br>1 Jacinth<br>8 Bars of Velium<br>1 Vial of Purified Mana (1 Poison Vial, 4 Rubies)<br>1 Small Block of Clay<br>1 Water Flask<br><br>Combine 1 Gem with 2 Bars of Velium (UNSTACKED) in a jewelers bag (OMG use for the 3rd slot at last) (Trivial around 185 JC) = Mounted Gem<br><br>Do that for all 4 gems<br><br>Combine the Vial of Mana (Chanter Made) with the gems, the clay and water in a potters wheel. Trivial about 135 Pottery = Unfired Seal<br><br>Fire with HQ Sheet in Kiln = Artisan's Seal!<br><br>All this is tradeable stuff, the only thing that becomes NO DROP is the hammer itself.<br><br>Each tradeskill (cept poison and alchemy :() can combine this seal with various BS items and if the skill level is high enough (you better be as close as you can stand to be to 250 in your tradeskill) it makes a no drop trophy item. All have the same stats (just like this one) but all have different names based on what skill you grandmastered to make them. All are NO DROP, the seals can be made for you, but the trophy YOU have to make. NONE of the items are LORE. SO YES YOU CAN HAVE 4 (Note: In AMMO slot these items do nothing, but all other 3 slots confirmed to work).<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue May 14 06:24:48 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>"And from the depths of the Seas of Odus rose a star, one that would shine light for all of Norrath.</td></tr>
